verses.text: And it came to pass a long time after that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had given rest unto Israel from all their enemies round about , that Joshua waxed old \add and\add* stricken in age.\f + \fr 23.1 \ft stricken…: Heb. come into days\f*
And Joshua called for all Israel , \add and\add* for their elders , and for their heads , and for their judges , and for their officers , and said unto them, I am old \add and\add* stricken in age :

And ye have seen all that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath done unto all these nations because of you; for the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God \add is\add* he that hath fought for you.

Behold , I have divided unto you by lot these nations that remain , to be an inheritance for your tribes , from Jordan , with all the nations that I have cut off , even unto the great sea westward.\f + \fr 23.4 \ft westward: Heb. at the sunset\f*

And the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God , he shall expel them from before you, and drive them from out of your sight ; and ye shall possess their land , as the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath promised unto you.
Be ye therefore very courageous to keep and to do all that is written in the book of the law of Moses , that ye turn not aside therefrom \add to\add* the right hand or \add to\add* the left ;

That ye come not among these nations , these that remain among you; neither make mention of the name of their gods , nor cause to swear \add by them\add*, neither serve them, nor bow yourselves unto them:
But cleave unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God , as ye have done unto this day.\f + \fr 23.8 \ft But cleave…: or, For if ye will cleave, etc\f*

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath driven out from before you great nations and strong : but \add as for\add* you, no man hath been able to stand before you unto this day.\f + \fr 23.9 \ft For the \+nd LORD\+nd*…: or, Then the \+nd LORD\+nd* will drive\f*
One man of you shall chase a thousand : for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God , he \add it is\add* that fighteth for you, as he hath promised you. \p
Take good heed therefore unto yourselves , that ye love the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God.\f + \fr 23.11 \ft yourselves: Heb. your souls\f*

Else if ye do in any wise go back , and cleave unto the remnant of these nations , \add even\add* these that remain among you, and shall make marriages with them, and go in unto them, and they to you:

Know for a certainty that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God will no more drive out \add any of\add* these nations from before you; but they shall be snares and traps unto you, and scourges in your sides , and thorns in your eyes , until ye perish from off this good land which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath given you.

And, behold, this day I \add am\add* going the way of all the earth : and ye know in all your hearts and in all your souls , that not one thing hath failed of all the good things which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God spake concerning you; all are come to pass unto you, \add and\add* not one thing hath failed thereof.

Therefore it shall come to pass, \add that\add* as all good things are come upon you, which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God promised you; so shall the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* bring upon you all evil things , until he have destroyed you from off this good land which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God hath given you.

When ye have transgressed the covenant of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* your God , which he commanded you, and have gone and served other gods , and bowed yourselves to them; then shall the anger of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* be kindled against you, and ye shall perish quickly from off the good land which he hath given unto you.
